subSubSection.paragraph:
Head
.

— Brown to reddish-brown. Impunctate, with significant transverse impression between posterior third of eyes. Eyes small, convex. Labial palpi slender and maxillary palpi enlarged (
Fig. 37a
), occasionally dark brown. Labrum and mandibulae contrasting dark brown. Antennae elongated, extended to the apical third of the elytra (
Figs. 38
, 
45
), the median antennomeres significantly broadened. Antennae entirely black and only the first basal antennomeres usually contrasting reddish-brown. First antennomere club shaped; second and third antennomere varied from a bit shorter to more or less the same length; ratio length of second to third antennomere 0.60–1.00 (mean: 0.79); ratio length of third to fourth antennomere 0.30–0.50 (mean: 0.42; 
Figs. 39
, 
46
).
